tasks-v2.md:159:[ ] TASK-067: Implementar `GET /api/v1/carrinho/{carrinhoId}` e tratar ID ausente.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-160-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md:161:[ ] TASK-068: Implementar descarte do vínculo local quando a consulta do carrinho retornar `404`.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-162-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md:163:[ ] TASK-069: Implementar hidratação deduplicada e paralela dos produtos únicos do carrinho.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-164-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-165-[ ] TASK-070: Implementar CartItem com imagem, título, preço, quantidade e fallback de produto.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-166-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md:167:[ ] TASK-071: Implementar página do carrinho com lista, subtotal, total e estado vazio.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-168-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-169-[ ] TASK-072: Implementar atualização de quantidade por PATCH com rollback em caso de falha.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-170-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-171-[ ] TASK-073: Implementar confirmação e remoção de item por DELETE com rollback em caso de falha.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-172-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md:173:[ ] TASK-074: Implementar badge do Header derivado do carrinho confirmado.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-174-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md:175:[ ] TASK-075: Invalidar e atualizar os caches necessários após cada mutação do carrinho.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-176-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-177-### Fase 5 — Checkout\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-178-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-179-[ ] TASK-076: Criar schemas de formulário para endereço de entrega e formas Pix, Cartao e Boleto.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-180-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md:181:[ ] TASK-077: Impedir acesso ao checkout sem sessão válida ou com carrinho vazio.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-182-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-183-[ ] TASK-078: Pré-carregar o endereço do checkout pelo perfil do cliente.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-184-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-185-[ ] TASK-079: Implementar a página de checkout com endereço editável apenas para o pedido atual.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-186-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md:187:[ ] TASK-080: Criar adapter de `CreatePedidoRequest` sem `clienteId` e sem `carrinhoId`.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-188-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md:189:[ ] TASK-081: Montar os itens do pedido a partir do último estado confirmado do carrinho.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-190-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-191-[ ] TASK-082: Implementar `POST /api/v1/pedido` com data ISO gerada no envio.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-192-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-193-[ ] TASK-083: Bloquear submissões duplicadas e tratar `409` e `422` no checkout.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-194-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md:195:[ ] TASK-084: Limpar o vínculo local do carrinho e invalidar pedidos após criação bem-sucedida.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-196-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-197-[ ] TASK-085: Implementar página de confirmação com dados retornados em `PedidoCriadoResponse`.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-198-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-199-### Fase 6 — Conta do cliente\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-200-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-201-[ ] TASK-086: Criar schemas e adapters de detalhe, atualização e ID do cliente.\r\n--\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-249-[ ] TASK-108: Testar `authStore`, expiração, escolha de storage e migração de versão.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-250-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-251-[ ] TASK-109: Testar `cartSessionStore`, troca de cliente, ID inválido e migração de versão.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-252-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-253-[ ] TASK-110: Testar componentes base por teclado, foco, estados e nomes acessíveis.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-254-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md:255:[ ] TASK-111: Testar integração de login, logout, `401` e retorno seguro com MSW.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-256-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-257-[ ] TASK-112: Testar integração de cadastro e perfil com respostas `201`, `409` e `422`.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-258-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-259-[ ] TASK-113: Testar integração de catálogo, categoria, busca, paginação e produto `404` com MSW.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-260-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md:261:[ ] TASK-114: Testar criação, leitura, atualização, remoção e rollback do carrinho com MSW.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-262-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md:263:[ ] TASK-115: Testar checkout e criação de pedido sem `clienteId` e `carrinhoId` no payload.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-264-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-265-[ ] TASK-116: Testar lista, detalhe e cancelamento recusado de pedido com MSW.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-266-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md:267:[ ] TASK-117: Criar E2E de cadastro, login, rota protegida e logout.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-268-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md:269:[ ] TASK-118: Criar E2E de visitante redirecionado ao login antes de adicionar um produto.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-270-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md:271:[ ] TASK-119: Criar E2E de adicionar, alterar quantidade e remover item do carrinho.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-272-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md:273:[ ] TASK-120: Criar E2E de carrinho, checkout e confirmação do pedido.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-274-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-275-[ ] TASK-121: Criar E2E de edição de dados e troca de senha.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-276-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-277-[ ] TASK-122: Criar E2E de consulta, detalhe e tentativa de cancelamento de pedido.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-278-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-279-[ ] TASK-123: Criar E2E de sessão expirada durante acesso protegido.\r\n---RETURNTO---\r\nexport type LoginLocationState = {\r\n  returnTo?: unknown\r\n  registrationSucceeded?: unknown\r\n}\r\n\r\nexport function hasRegistrationSucceeded(state: unknown) {\r\n  return (state as LoginLocationState | null)?.registrationSucceeded === true\r\n}\r\n\r\nexport function getInternalReturnTo(state: unknown, fallback = '/') {\r\n  const returnTo = (state as LoginLocationState | null)?.returnTo\r\n\r\n  if (typeof returnTo !== 'string' || !returnTo.startsWith('/') || returnTo.startsWith('//')) {\r\n    return fallback\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  try {\r\n    const url = new URL(returnTo, 'https://shop-api.local')\r\n\r\n    return url.origin === 'https://shop-api.local' && !returnTo.includes('\\\\')\r\n      ? `${url.pathname}${url.search}${url.hash}`\r\n      : fallback\r\n  } catch {\r\n    return fallback\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n\r\nimport { describe, expect, it } from 'vitest'\r\n\r\nimport { getInternalReturnTo } from './returnTo'\r\n\r\ndescribe('getInternalReturnTo', () => {\r\n  it.each([\r\n    ['/checkout?etapa=pagamento#resumo', '/checkout?etapa=pagamento#resumo'],\r\n    ['https://malicioso.example/roubo', '/'],\r\n    ['//malicioso.example/roubo', '/'],\r\n    ['/\\\\malicioso.example/roubo', '/'],\r\n    ['javascript:alert(1)', '/'],\r\n    [undefined, '/'],\r\n  ])('normalizes %s to an internal destination', (returnTo, expected) => {\r\n    expect(getInternalReturnTo({ returnTo })).toBe(expected)\r\n  })\r\n})\r\n\r\n---LOGIN---\r\nimport { useForm } from 'react-hook-form'\r\nimport { Link, useLocation, useNavigate } from 'react-router-dom'\r\n\r\nimport { Button } from '../../../shared/ui/buttons/Button'\r\nimport { InlineAlert } from '../../../shared/ui/feedback/InlineAlert'\r\nimport { FormErrorSummary } from '../../../shared/ui/forms/FormErrorSummary'\r\nimport { Input } from '../../../shared/ui/forms/Input'\r\nimport { loginRequestSchema, type LoginRequest } from '../contracts/login'\r\nimport { useLoginMutation } from '../mutations/useLoginMutation'\r\nimport { getInternalReturnTo, hasRegistrationSucceeded } from '../routing/returnTo'\r\nimport { useAuthStore } from '../store/authStore'\r\n\r\nconst EMAIL_REQUIRED_MESSAGE = 'Informe seu e-mail.'\r\nconst EMAIL_INVALID_MESSAGE = 'Informe um e-mail válido.'\r\nconst PASSWORD_REQUIRED_MESSAGE = 'Informe sua senha.'\r\n\r\ntype LoginFormValues = LoginRequest & {\r\n  manterConectado: boolean\r\n}\r\n\r\nexport function LoginPage() {\r\n  const setSession = useAuthStore((state) => state.setSession)\r\n  const location = useLocation()\r\n  const navigate = useNavigate()\r\n  const loginMutation = useLoginMutation()\r\n  const {\r\n    register,\r\n    handleSubmit,\r\n    reset,\r\n    resetField,\r\n    formState: { errors },\r\n  } = useForm<LoginFormValues>({\r\n    defaultValues: { manterConectado: false },\r\n  })\r\n\r\n  const submitLogin = handleSubmit(async (values) => {\r\n    const parsedValues = loginRequestSchema.safeParse(values)\r\n\r\n    if (!parsedValues.success) return\r\n\r\n    try {\r\n      const session = await loginMutation.mutateAsync(parsedValues.data)\r\n      setSession(session, values.manterConectado ? 'local' : 'session')\r\n      reset()\r\n      navigate(getInternalReturnTo(location.state), { replace: true })\r\n    } catch {\r\n      // The mutation error is rendered in the form summary.\r\n    } finally {\r\n      resetField('senha')\r\n    }\r\n  })\r\n\r\n  const formErrors = [\r\n    errors.email?.message ? { fieldId: 'login-email', message: errors.email.message } : null,\r\n    errors.senha?.message ? { fieldId: 'login-password', message: errors.senha.message } : null,\r\n    loginMutation.error ? { message: loginMutation.error.message } : null,\r\n  ].filter((error): error is { fieldId?: string; message: string } => error !== null)\r\n\r\n  return (\r\n    <section className=\"container-page flex min-h-dvh items-center justify-center py-12 sm:py-16\">\r\n      <div className=\"w-full max-w-md rounded-2xl border border-ink-700/80 bg-ink-850 p-6 shadow-2xl shadow-black/40 sm:p-8\">\r\n        <div className=\"text-center\">\r\n          <span\r\n            aria-hidden=\"true\"\r\n            className=\"inline-grid size-12 place-items-center rounded-2xl bg-brand-500 text-xl font-black text-ink-950\"\r\n          >\r\n            S\r\n          </span>\r\n          <h1 className=\"mt-5 text-2xl font-bold text-zinc-50\">Entrar na sua conta</h1>\r\n          <p className=\"mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-400\">\r\n            Bem-vindo de volta. Acesse seus pedidos e dados.\r\n          </p>\r\n        </div>\r\n\r\n        {hasRegistrationSucceeded(location.state) ? (\r\n          <InlineAlert className=\"mt-6\" title=\"Cadastro concluído\" variant=\"success\">\r\n            Sua conta foi criada. Entre com as credenciais cadastradas.\r\n          </InlineAlert>\r\n        ) : null}\r\n\r\n        <form className=\"mt-8 space-y-5\" noValidate onSubmit={submitLogin}>\r\n          <FormErrorSummary errors={formErrors} />\r\n          <Input\r\n            id=\"login-email\"\r\n            label=\"E-mail\"\r\n            type=\"email\"\r\n            autoComplete=\"email\"\r\n            placeholder=\"voce@email.com\"\r\n            error={errors.email?.message}\r\n            {...register('email', {\r\n              required: EMAIL_REQUIRED_MESSAGE,\r\n              validate: (value) =>\r\n                loginRequestSchema.shape.email.safeParse(value).success || EMAIL_INVALID_MESSAGE,\r\n            })}\r\n          />\r\n          <Input\r\n            id=\"login-password\"\r\n            label=\"Senha\"\r\n            type=\"password\"\r\n            autoComplete=\"current-password\"\r\n            placeholder=\"••••••••\"\r\n            error={errors.senha?.message}\r\n            {...register('senha', { required: PASSWORD_REQUIRED_MESSAGE })}\r\n          />\r\n          <label className=\"flex w-fit cursor-pointer items-center gap-2 text-sm text-zinc-300\">\r\n            <input\r\n              className=\"size-4 rounded border-ink-600 accent-brand-500\"\r\n              type=\"checkbox\"\r\n              {...register('manterConectado')}\r\n            />\r\n            Manter conectado\r\n          </label>\r\n          <Button className=\"w-full\" disabled={loginMutation.isPending} type=\"submit\">\r\n            {loginMutation.isPending ? 'Entrando…' : 'Entrar'}\r\n          </Button>\r\n        </form>\r\n\r\n        <p className=\"mt-6 border-t border-ink-700/70 pt-6 text-center text-sm text-zinc-400\">\r\n          Não tem conta?{' '}\r\n          <Link className=\"font-medium text-brand-400 hover:text-brand-300\" to=\"/cadastro\">\r\n            Criar agora\r\n          </Link>\r\n        </p>\r\n      </div>\r\n    </section>\r\n  )\r\n}\r\n\r\nimport { QueryClient, QueryClientProvider } from '@tanstack/react-query'\r\nimport { fireEvent, render, screen, waitFor } from '@testing-library/react'\r\nimport { http, HttpResponse } from 'msw'\r\nimport type { PropsWithChildren } from 'react'\r\nimport { MemoryRouter } from 'react-router-dom'\r\nimport { beforeEach, describe, expect, it, vi } from 'vitest'\r\n\r\nimport { server } from '../../../shared/testing/server'\r\nimport { useAuthStore } from '../store/authStore'\r\nimport { LoginPage } from './LoginPage'\r\n\r\nfunction renderPage(initialState?: unknown) {\r\n  const queryClient = new QueryClient({\r\n    defaultOptions: { mutations: { retry: false } },\r\n  })\r\n  const wrapper = ({ children }: PropsWithChildren) => (\r\n    <MemoryRouter initialEntries={[{ pathname: '/entrar', state: initialState }]}>\r\n      <QueryClientProvider client={queryClient}>{children}</QueryClientProvider>\r\n    </MemoryRouter>\r\n  )\r\n\r\n  return render(<LoginPage />, { wrapper })\r\n}\r\n\r\ndescribe('LoginPage', () => {\r\n  beforeEach(() => {\r\n    useAuthStore.getState().clearSession()\r\n    vi.stubEnv('VITE_API_BASE_URL', 'https://api.example.com')\r\n  })\r\n\r\n  it('shows the registration confirmation received through navigation state', () => {\r\n    renderPage({ registrationSucceeded: true })\r\n\r\n    expect(screen.getByRole('status')).toHaveTextContent('Cadastro concluído')\r\n    expect(screen.getByRole('status')).toHaveTextContent(\r\n      'Sua conta foi criada. Entre com as credenciais cadastradas.',\r\n    )\r\n  })\r\n\r\n  it('validates credentials before sending the login request', async () => {\r\n    let requests = 0\r\n    server.use(\r\n      http.post('https://api.example.com/api/v1/auth/login', () => {\r\n        requests += 1\r\n        return HttpResponse.json({})\r\n      }),\r\n    )\r\n    renderPage()\r\n\r\n    fireEvent.change(screen.getByLabelText('E-mail'), { target: { value: 'email-invalido' } })\r\n    fireEvent.click(screen.getByRole('button', { name: 'Entrar' }))\r\n\r\n    expect(await screen.findAllByText('Informe um e-mail válido.')).toHaveLength(2)\r\n    expect(screen.getAllByText('Informe sua senha.')).toHaveLength(2)\r\n    expect(requests).toBe(0)\r\n  })\r\n\r\n  it.each([\r\n    { keepConnected: false, persistence: 'session' as const },\r\n    { keepConnected: true, persistence: 'local' as const },\r\n  ])('stores the session using $persistence persistence', async ({ keepConnected, persistence }) => {\r\n    server.use(\r\n      http.post('https://api.example.com/api/v1/auth/login', () =>\r\n        HttpResponse.json({\r\n          status: true,\r\n          data: {\r\n            token: 'header.payload.signature',\r\n            tipo: 'Bearer',\r\n            expiraEm: '2026-07-14T18:00:00-03:00',\r\n            usuarioId: 10,\r\n            clienteId: 20,\r\n            email: 'cliente@exemplo.com',\r\n          },\r\n        }),\r\n      ),\r\n    )\r\n    renderPage()\r\n\r\n    fireEvent.change(screen.getByLabelText('E-mail'), {\r\n      target: { value: 'cliente@exemplo.com' },\r\n    })\r\n    fireEvent.change(screen.getByLabelText('Senha'), { target: { value: 'senha-secreta' } })\r\n    if (keepConnected) {\r\n      fireEvent.click(screen.getByRole('checkbox', { name: 'Manter conectado' }))\r\n    }\r\n    fireEvent.click(screen.getByRole('button', { name: 'Entrar' }))\r\n\r\n    await waitFor(() => expect(useAuthStore.getState().session?.clienteId).toBe(20))\r\n    expect(useAuthStore.getState().persistence).toBe(persistence)\r\n    expect(screen.getByLabelText('E-mail')).toHaveValue('')\r\n    expect(screen.getByLabelText('Senha')).toHaveValue('')\r\n    expect(screen.getByRole('checkbox', { name: 'Manter conectado' })).not.toBeChecked()\r\n  })\r\n\r\n  it('shows an authentication error and has no password recovery action', async () => {\r\n    server.use(\r\n      http.post('https://api.example.com/api/v1/auth/login', () =>\r\n        HttpResponse.json(\r\n          { error: { message: 'E-mail ou senha inválidos.' } },\r\n          { status: 401 },\r\n        ),\r\n      ),\r\n    )\r\n    renderPage()\r\n\r\n    fireEvent.change(screen.getByLabelText('E-mail'), {\r\n      target: { value: 'cliente@exemplo.com' },\r\n    })\r\n    fireEvent.change(screen.getByLabelText('Senha'), { target: { value: 'senha-incorreta' } })\r\n    fireEvent.click(screen.getByRole('button', { name: 'Entrar' }))\r\n\r\n    expect(await screen.findByText('E-mail ou senha inválidos.')).toBeInTheDocument()\r\n    expect(screen.getByLabelText('E-mail')).toHaveValue('cliente@exemplo.com')\r\n    expect(screen.getByLabelText('Senha')).toHaveValue('')\r\n    expect(screen.queryByText(/esqueci|recuper/i)).not.toBeInTheDocument()\r\n    expect(screen.getByRole('link', { name: 'Criar agora' })).toHaveAttribute('href', '/cadastro')\r\n  })\r\n})\r\n\r\n---GUARD---\r\nimport { Navigate, Outlet, useLocation } from 'react-router-dom'\r\n\r\nimport { isAuthSessionExpired, useAuthStore } from '../store/authStore'\r\n\r\nexport function ProtectedRoute() {\r\n  const session = useAuthStore((state) => state.session)\r\n  const location = useLocation()\r\n\r\n  if (!session || isAuthSessionExpired(session)) {\r\n    const returnTo = `${location.pathname}${location.search}${location.hash}`\r\n\r\n    return <Navigate replace state={{ returnTo }} to=\"/entrar\" />\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  return <Outlet />\r\n}\r\n\r\nimport { render, screen } from '@testing-library/react'\r\nimport { MemoryRouter, Route, Routes, useLocation } from 'react-router-dom'\r\nimport { beforeEach, describe, expect, it } from 'vitest'\r\n\r\nimport { useAuthStore, type AuthSession } from '../store/authStore'\r\nimport { ProtectedRoute } from './ProtectedRoute'\r\n\r\nconst session: AuthSession = {\r\n  token: 'header.payload.signature',\r\n  tipo: 'Bearer',\r\n  expiraEm: '2099-01-01T00:00:00Z',\r\n  usuarioId: 10,\r\n  clienteId: 20,\r\n  email: 'cliente@exemplo.com',\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction LoginDestination() {\r\n  const location = useLocation()\r\n\r\n  return <p>{`${location.pathname}|${String(location.state?.returnTo)}`}</p>\r\n}\r\n\r\nfunction renderProtectedRoute() {\r\n  return render(\r\n    <MemoryRouter initialEntries={['/checkout?etapa=pagamento#resumo']}>\r\n      <Routes>\r\n        <Route element={<ProtectedRoute />}>\r\n          <Route path=\"checkout\" element={<h1>Checkout protegido</h1>} />\r\n        </Route>\r\n        <Route path=\"entrar\" element={<LoginDestination />} />\r\n      </Routes>\r\n    </MemoryRouter>,\r\n  )\r\n}\r\n\r\ndescribe('ProtectedRoute', () => {\r\n  beforeEach(() => useAuthStore.getState().clearSession())\r\n\r\n  it('redirects a visitor to login preserving only the current internal location', () => {\r\n    renderProtectedRoute()\r\n\r\n    expect(screen.getByText('/entrar|/checkout?etapa=pagamento#resumo')).toBeInTheDocument()\r\n  })\r\n\r\n  it('renders the protected route for an authenticated customer', () => {\r\n    useAuthStore.getState().setSession(session, 'session')\r\n    renderProtectedRoute()\r\n\r\n    expect(screen.getByRole('heading', { name: 'Checkout protegido' })).toBeInTheDocument()\r\n  })\r\n\r\n  it('redirects when the stored session is expired', () => {\r\n    useAuthStore.getState().setSession({ ...session, expiraEm: '2020-01-01T00:00:00Z' }, 'session')\r\n    renderProtectedRoute()\r\n\r\n    expect(screen.getByText('/entrar|/checkout?etapa=pagamento#resumo')).toBeInTheDocument()\r\n  })\r\n})\r\n\r\n---ROUTER---\r\nimport { Route, Routes } from 'react-router-dom'\r\n\r\nimport { AccountLayout } from '../layouts/AccountLayout'\r\nimport { LoginPage } from '../../features/auth/pages/LoginPage'\r\nimport { RegistrationPage } from '../../features/customer/pages/RegistrationPage'\r\nimport { ProtectedRoute } from '../../features/auth/routing/ProtectedRoute'\r\nimport { PublicLayout } from '../layouts/PublicLayout'\r\nimport { StoreLayout } from '../layouts/StoreLayout'\r\nimport { NotFoundPage } from './NotFoundPage'\r\nimport { RoutePlaceholder } from './RoutePlaceholder'\r\n\r\nexport function AppRouter() {\r\n  return (\r\n    <Routes>\r\n      <Route element={<StoreLayout />}>\r\n        <Route index element={<RoutePlaceholder title=\"Catálogo\" />} />\r\n        <Route path=\"produtos/:produtoId\" element={<RoutePlaceholder title=\"Produto\" />} />\r\n        <Route element={<ProtectedRoute />}>\r\n          <Route path=\"carrinho\" element={<RoutePlaceholder title=\"Carrinho\" />} />\r\n          <Route path=\"checkout\" element={<RoutePlaceholder title=\"Checkout\" />} />\r\n          <Route\r\n            path=\"pedido-confirmado/:pedidoId\"\r\n            element={<RoutePlaceholder title=\"Pedido confirmado\" />}\r\n          />\r\n          <Route path=\"pedidos\" element={<RoutePlaceholder title=\"Pedidos\" />} />\r\n          <Route path=\"pedidos/:pedidoId\" element={<RoutePlaceholder title=\"Detalhes do pedido\" />} />\r\n          <Route path=\"minha-conta\" element={<AccountLayout />}>\r\n            <Route path=\"dados\" element={<RoutePlaceholder title=\"Dados pessoais\" />} />\r\n            <Route path=\"senha\" element={<RoutePlaceholder title=\"Alterar senha\" />} />\r\n          </Route>\r\n        </Route>\r\n      </Route>\r\n\r\n      <Route element={<PublicLayout />}>\r\n        <Route path=\"entrar\" element={<LoginPage />} />\r\n        <Route path=\"cadastro\" element={<RegistrationPage />} />\r\n        <Route path=\"*\" element={<NotFoundPage />} />\r\n      </Route>\r\n    </Routes>\r\n  )\r\n}\r\n\r\n---PACKAGE---\r\n{\r\n  \"name\": \"shop-api-frontend\",\r\n  \"private\": true,\r\n  \"version\": \"0.0.0\",\r\n  \"type\": \"module\",\r\n  \"scripts\": {\r\n    \"dev\": \"vite\",\r\n    \"build\": \"vite build\",\r\n    \"typecheck\": \"tsc -b\",\r\n    \"lint\": \"eslint .\",\r\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\",\r\n    \"test:watch\": \"vitest\",\r\n    \"test:e2e\": \"playwright test\",\r\n    \"preview\": \"vite preview\"\r\n  },\r\n  \"dependencies\": {\r\n    \"@tanstack/react-query\": \"^5.101.2\",\r\n    \"react\": \"^19.0.0\",\r\n    \"react-dom\": \"^19.0.0\",\r\n    \"react-hook-form\": \"^7.81.0\",\r\n    \"react-router-dom\": \"^7.18.1\",\r\n    \"zod\": \"^4.4.3\",\r\n    \"zustand\": \"^5.0.14\"\r\n  },\r\n  \"devDependencies\": {\r\n    \"@eslint/js\": \"^10.0.1\",\r\n    \"@playwright/test\": \"^1.61.1\",\r\n    \"@tailwindcss/vite\": \"^4.3.2\",\r\n    \"@testing-library/jest-dom\": \"^6.9.1\",\r\n    \"@testing-library/react\": \"^16.3.2\",\r\n    \"@types/react\": \"^19.0.2\",\r\n    \"@types/react-dom\": \"^19.0.2\",\r\n    \"@vitejs/plugin-react\": \"^4.3.4\",\r\n    \"eslint\": \"^10.7.0\",\r\n    \"eslint-plugin-react-hooks\": \"^7.1.1\",\r\n    \"eslint-plugin-react-refresh\": \"^0.5.3\",\r\n    \"globals\": \"^17.7.0\",\r\n    \"jsdom\": \"^29.1.1\",\r\n    \"msw\": \"^2.15.0\",\r\n    \"tailwindcss\": \"^4.3.2\",\r\n    \"typescript\": \"~5.7.2\",\r\n    \"typescript-eslint\": \"^8.64.0\",\r\n    \"vite\": \"^6.0.5\",\r\n    \"vitest\": \"^4.1.10\"\r\n  },\r\n  \"msw\": {\r\n    \"workerDirectory\": [\r\n      \"public\"\r\n    ]\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n\r\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
{"type":"item.started","item":{"id":"item_6","type":"command_execution","command":"\"C:\\\\Program Files\\\\PowerShell\\\\7\\\\pwsh.exe\" -Command \"rg -n -C 4 \\\"TASK-059|TASK-060|TASK-061|Após autenticar|sem adicionar|returnTo\\\" docs/frontend-tasks-v2.md docs/frontend-specification-v2.md docs/frontend-implementation-plan-v2.md; Write-Output '---PRODUCT FILES---'; rg --files frontend/src/features | rg \\\"product|catalog|Product|produto\\\"; Write-Output '---ADD FLOW---'; rg -n -C 8 \\\"adicionar|Adicionar|returnTo|entrar|navigate\\\" frontend/src\"","aggregated_output":"","exit_code":null,"status":"in_progress"}}
{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_6","type":"command_execution","command":"\"C:\\\\Program Files\\\\PowerShell\\\\7\\\\pwsh.exe\" -Command \"rg -n -C 4 \\\"TASK-059|TASK-060|TASK-061|Após autenticar|sem adicionar|returnTo\\\" docs/frontend-tasks-v2.md docs/frontend-specification-v2.md docs/frontend-implementation-plan-v2.md; Write-Output '---PRODUCT FILES---'; rg --files frontend/src/features | rg \\\"product|catalog|Product|produto\\\"; Write-Output '---ADD FLOW---'; rg -n -C 8 \\\"adicionar|Adicionar|returnTo|entrar|navigate\\\" frontend/src\"","aggregated_output":"docs/frontend-implementation-plan-v2.md-110-- O token é anexado somente às rotas protegidas.\r\ndocs/frontend-implementation-plan-v2.md-111-- `expiraEm` é verificado na inicialização e antes de mutations protegidas.\r\ndocs/frontend-implementation-plan-v2.md-112-- A opção de permanência escolhe `localStorage` ou `sessionStorage`.\r\ndocs/frontend-implementation-plan-v2.md-113-- Não haverá refresh silencioso, pois a API não expõe refresh token.\r\ndocs/frontend-implementation-plan-v2.md:114:- `401` encerra a sessão e conserva apenas um `returnTo` interno.\r\ndocs/frontend-implementation-plan-v2.md-115-- Logout remoto é tentado antes da limpeza, sem impedir a limpeza local.\r\ndocs/frontend-implementation-plan-v2.md-116-- Mudança de `clienteId` remove o vínculo de carrinho do usuário anterior da memória ativa.\r\ndocs/frontend-implementation-plan-v2.md-117-\r\ndocs/frontend-implementation-plan-v2.md-118-### 4.5 Estratégia de carrinho\r\n--\ndocs/frontend-specification-v2.md-58-## 4. Usuário e jornadas\ndocs/frontend-specification-v2.md-59-\ndocs/frontend-specification-v2.md-60-### 4.1 Visitante\ndocs/frontend-specification-v2.md-61-\ndocs/frontend-specification-v2.md:62:Pode consultar categorias, buscar produtos, paginar resultados, abrir o detalhe e criar uma conta. Ao tentar adicionar um produto, deve ser encaminhado ao login, sem criar ou persistir itens localmente. Após autenticar-se, retorna à rota de origem e pode repetir a ação.\ndocs/frontend-specification-v2.md-63-\ndocs/frontend-specification-v2.md-64-### 4.2 Cliente autenticado\ndocs/frontend-specification-v2.md-65-\ndocs/frontend-specification-v2.md-66-Pode criar e gerenciar o carrinho, finalizar uma compra, consultar e cancelar pedidos, alterar dados pessoais, trocar a senha, cancelar a conta e encerrar a sessão.\n--\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-93-[x] TASK-036: Implementar a página de login sem ação de recuperação de senha.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-94-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-95-[x] TASK-037: Implementar opção “manter conectado” e limpeza segura do formulário de login.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-96-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md:97:[x] TASK-038: Implementar ProtectedRoute com `returnTo` limitado a rotas internas.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-98-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-99-[x] TASK-039: Implementar tratamento global de `401` com limpeza de caches privados e redirecionamento.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-100-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-101-[x] TASK-040: Implementar logout remoto e limpeza local resiliente a token expirado.\r\n--\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-137-[ ] TASK-057: Implementar query de detalhe por `produtoId` com tratamento de `404`.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-138-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-139-[ ] TASK-058: Implementar página de produto com título, categoria, modelo, descrição, foto, preço e estoque.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-140-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md:141:[ ] TASK-059: Integrar QuantityInput ao estoque inteiro disponível e ao estado esgotado.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-142-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md:143:[ ] TASK-060: Implementar o guard que envia visitantes ao login antes de qualquer inclusão no carrinho.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-144-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md:145:[ ] TASK-061: Implementar o retorno à página de origem após o login sem adicionar item automaticamente.\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-146-\r\ndocs/frontend-tasks-v2.md-147-### Fase 4 